'''Random access memory'''
# A computer memory chip that dynamically stores program and data values during operation. Each byte of memory may be directly accessed.
# The main memory of a computer available for program execution or data storage.
# Any computer memory that allows direct access to any of its values, without having to read other non-relevant values before reading the required data value.

